================================================================================
Third-party acknowledgements
================================================================================

This project depends on a number of open-source libraries. The full list is
declared in app/package.json (frontend) and lasca-report-pdf-service/
requirements.txt (PDF service). Notable runtime dependencies include:

  - Next.js (MIT) — https://nextjs.org/
  - React (MIT) — https://react.dev/
  - Vercel AI SDK (Apache-2.0) — https://sdk.vercel.ai/
  - paged.js (MIT) — https://pagedjs.org/
  - Supabase JS client (MIT) — https://supabase.com/
  - Anthropic SDK (MIT) and OpenAI SDK (MIT)
  - Playwright (Apache-2.0) — https://playwright.dev/

Bundled fonts (PDF service, optional `fonts/` directory):

  - LXGW WenKai (SIL Open Font License 1.1) —
    https://github.com/lxgw/LxgwWenKai
  - Lora (SIL Open Font License 1.1) — https://github.com/cyrealtype/Lora-Cyrillic
  - Outfit (SIL Open Font License 1.1) — https://github.com/Outfitio/Outfit-Fonts
  - Noto Sans SC (SIL Open Font License 1.1) —
    https://fonts.google.com/noto/specimen/Noto+Sans+SC

Apple system fonts referenced by the macOS-only fallback path in
`report_engine.py` (e.g. STHeiti, Kaiti) are NOT bundled. They are loaded at
runtime from the host OS only when present, and are not redistributable.
